\n\n<li><strong><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/indexnow/\" title=\"IndexNow\">IndexNow</a></strong>: For fast indexing on search engines that support the IndexNow protocol (like Bing and Yandex).</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/smart-xml-sitemaps/\" title=\"Smart XML Sitemaps\">Sitemap generator</a></strong>: Automatically generate different types of sitemaps to notify all search engines of any updates on your site.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/\" title=\"Features\">And more</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO also has other powerful tools to help you master your <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/on-page-seo-checklist-wordpress/\" title=\"On-Page SEO Checklist: The Easy Way to Optimize WordPress Content\">on-page SEO</a>, off-page SEO, and even <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/what-is-technical-seo-the-best-checklist-in-2022/\" title=\"What Is Technical SEO? The Best Checklist in 2023\">technical SEO</a>. The best part about AIOSEO is that it’s a no-code SEO plugin. This means you can use it to perform most SEO tasks even if you don’t have any technical or coding knowledge.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For step-by-step instructions on how to install AIOSEO, check out our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/installing-all-in-one-seo-pro/\">installation guide</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Check out our article on the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-wordpress-plugins/\" title=\"32 Best WordPress Plugins in 2024 [Paid and Free]\">best WordPress plugins</a> for more tools to help you manage your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"aioseo-boost-your-google-e-e-a-t-signals-with-author-seo\">2. Boost Your Google E-E-A-T Signals with Author SEO</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Implementing Google&#8217;s E-E-A-T content quality guidelines is easier if you have a plugin like AIOSEO. This is thanks to the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/author-seo-google-e-e-a-t/\" title=\"Author SEO – Google E-E-A-T Addon\">Author SEO module</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"high\" width=\"700\" height=\"403\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/edit-user.png\" alt=\"Author SEO module in AIOSEO.\" class=\"wp-image-268292\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/edit-user.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/edit-user-300x173.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/edit-user-600x345.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This module enables you to add information to your user profiles:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"496\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-info-1.png\" alt=\"Author info to be filled.\" class=\"wp-image-268293\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-info-1.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-info-1-300x212.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-info-1-600x424.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also add your areas of expertise:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"238\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/knows-about-section.png\" alt=\"Showcase your areas of expertise.\" class=\"wp-image-268294\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/knows-about-section.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/knows-about-section-300x102.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/knows-about-section-600x203.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>All this information points to your experience and expertise in your field. Plus, coupled with the JSON schema markup, it proves to search engines that you’re qualified to talk about the subject. This helps <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-boost-your-author-seo-in-wordpress/\" title=\"How to Boost Your Author SEO in WordPress\">boost your author SEO</a> and rank higher in searches around your keyword.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>All this information helps you demonstrate Google E-E-A-T, resulting in better rankings.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"aioseo-1-know-your-target-audience-and-what-theyre-looking-for\">3. Know Your Target Audience and What They’re Looking For</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the first ways to ensure that you’re creating E-E-A-T content is to know what your users are looking for when they input a search query.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Are they looking for information?</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Do they want to buy a product now?</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Are they checking out different products they want to buy soon?</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Are they looking for a particular website/web page?</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>The reason behind a search query is called search intent (or user intent).</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Understanding search intent is pretty easy. A couple of ways to do it include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Use Google</strong>: Google your keyword and check the type of content that appears in the top results. This is what Google deems the most relevant answers for that search term.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Use a Keyword research tool</strong>: Keyword research tools like <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/semrush/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"Semrush\">Semrush</a> show search intent as part of the keyword metrics.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Check keyword modifiers</strong>: Using a keyword research tool, check the keyword modifiers used the most in other related keywords or variations of your keyword.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you’ve figured out what <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-use-buyer-types-to-improve-web-content-and-boost-conversions/\" title=\"How to Use Buyer Types to Improve Web Content and Boost Conversions\">your audience</a> is looking for, create content that answers their questions fully.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"aioseo-2-create-data-rich-content\">4. Create Data-rich Content</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Another way to ensure that your content meets E-E-A-T requirements is to leverage data as much as possible. By citing facts and data from reputable sources, you show that your content is accurate. It also helps you showcase your expertise, make your content authoritative, and earn your readers&#8217; trust. Therefore, data is the perfect ingredient for creating E-E-A-T content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Besides citing other resources, you can also conduct your own research. This has the advantage of establishing you as an authority and expert in your field. It also helps you <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/link-building-guide/\" title=\"The Ultimate Link Building Guide You Need for 2023\">build backlinks</a> to your site, which brings us to the next point.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"aioseo-3-encourage-your-customers-to-leave-reviews-on-third-party-platforms\">5. Encourage Your Customers to Leave Reviews on Third-party Platforms</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Reviews are not just a powerful form of word-of-mouth marketing or social proof. They’re also a great way to build your website’s E-E-A-T, especially with <a href=\"https://developers.google.com/search/blog/2021/04/product-reviews-update\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">Google’s reviews update</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"700\" height=\"377\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/google-eat-reviews.png\" alt=\"Reviews are an essential ingredient to meeting Google E-E-A-T standards.\" class=\"wp-image-84905\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/google-eat-reviews.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/google-eat-reviews-300x162.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/google-eat-reviews-600x323.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"aioseo-4-build-relevant-backlinks-to-your-content\">6. Build Relevant Backlinks to Your Content</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Backlinks have been an <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/link-building-statistics/\" title=\"29 Link Building Statistics to Help Power Your SEO Strategy\">important ranking factor</a> since the inception of the internet. They’re also an essential element in creating E-E-A-T content. The main reason is that backlinks are a vote of confidence that your content is valuable and helpful. The more backlinks you build to a piece of content, the more authoritative it becomes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Note, however, that not all backlinks are created equal. You must build backlinks from high-authority sites relevant to your topic. Building backlinks from irrelevant backlinks will only signal to search engines that you’re simply building backlinks to game the system.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Reviews signal that users can trust you and that you&#8217;re an expert in your field. When your customers leave reviews (negative and positive), take time to respond to them. Doing so indicates that you’re reputable and committed to customer success.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"aioseo-5-include-author-bylines-to-gain-trust\">7. Include Author Bylines to Gain Trust</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>One way to encourage trust in your content is by giving authors bylines. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"717\" height=\"422\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/google-eat-author-bylines.png\" alt=\"Author bylines are an excellent way to boost your Google E-E-A-T score.\" class=\"wp-image-84906\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/google-eat-author-bylines.png 717w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/google-eat-author-bylines-300x177.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/google-eat-author-bylines-600x353.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 717px) 100vw, 717px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Readers and search engines alike want to know who’s responsible for creating a piece of content and whether they’re a reputable source or not. To improve the author&#8217;s trustworthiness, you can also include links to their social media profiles or website.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>On the same note, try to involve subject matter experts as much as possible in your content creation process. This will ensure that your content is accurate and helpful. It also makes it easier to pull on their experience. You can also leverage their credentials to boost your trust signals and further bolster the fact that the authors have first-hand experience with the topic.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"aioseo-6-improve-security-by-moving-to-https\">8. Improve Security By Moving to HTTPS</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If you haven’t yet, invest in <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/website-security/\" title=\"Website Security: 8 Tips to Make Your WordPress Website Secure\">your website’s security</a> by moving from the less secure HTTP protocol to the more secure HTTPS protocol. Doing this is another excellent way of proving that your site is trustworthy.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To move to HTTPS, you must invest in a Secure Socket Layer (SSL) certificate. An SSL certificate is a digital certificate that authenticates a website’s identity. More importantly, it provides an encrypted connection protecting your visitors from malicious actors. Some great places for getting free or affordable SSL certificates include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/really-simple-ssl/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Really Simple SSL</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/namecheap/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Namecheap</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/domain-com-ssl/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Domain.com</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Ensuring that your website is secure is an important way of improving your E-E-A-T score.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"aioseo-7-make-your-contact-details-easy-to-find\">9. Make Your Contact Details Easy to Find</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Another easy way to boost the trustworthiness of your website is by openly displaying your contact details. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"700\" height=\"287\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/google-eat-contact-details.png\" alt=\"Including your contact details on your website is another way you can meet Google E-E-A-T standards.\" class=\"wp-image-85037\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/google-eat-contact-details.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/google-eat-contact-details-300x123.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/google-eat-contact-details-600x246.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Particularly if you&#8217;re a location-based business, elements like your address and phone numbers signal to search engines and users that you are an entity they can trust.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>An added advantage of openly displaying your physical address is that it can also help <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/a-complete-local-seo-checklist/\" title=\"A Complete Local SEO Checklist: 10 Tips to Improve Rankings\">boost your local SEO</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also check out our guide on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-local-business-schema-in-wordpress/\" title=\"How to Add Local Business Schema in WordPress\">how to add Local Business schema</a>. Doing so will help you add your Google Maps location to your website, further bolstering your local SEO strategy. More importantly, it will also help you meet Google&#8217;s E-E-A-T standards.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"aioseo-google-e-a-t-the-blueprint-for-content-that-ranks-and-converts\">Google E-E-A-T: The Blueprint for Content that Ranks and Converts</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Understanding Google’s search quality rater guidelines is essential to helping you create effective content. Following these guidelines will help ensure that your content is competitive in search.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Examples of such guidelines are the E-E-A-T standards.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>By following the tips above, you can <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-come-up-with-great-content-ideas/\" title=\"How to Come up with Great Content Ideas\">create content that ranks well</a>. But more importantly, your content will offer users a positive experience, resulting in better conversion rates.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this article has helped you understand that coding and technical knowledge are not a necessity for you to master SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this article helped you know what Google E-E-A-T means. You may also want to check out other articles on our blog, like our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ultimate-wordpress-seo-guide/\" title=\"Ultimate WordPress SEO Guide: Optimize Your Site in 2023\">ultimate WordPress SEO guide</a> or our guide to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-start-a-small-business-blog/\" title=\"How to Start a Small Business Blog in 2023\">starting a small business blog</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you found this article helpful, then please subscribe to our <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/c/AIOSEO\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">YouTube Channel</a>. You’ll find many more helpful tutorials there. You can also follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/aioseopack\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">Twitter</a>, <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/aioseo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">LinkedIn</a>, or <a href=\"https://facebook.com/aioseopack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">Facebook</a> to stay in the loop.</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/what-is-google-eat/\">What is Google E-E-A-T?  Understanding Google’s Secret Sauce for Creating Effective Content</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:43:\"https://aioseo.com/what-is-google-eat/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:79:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:41:\"How to Boost Your Author SEO in WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:146:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-boost-your-author-seo-in-wordpress/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=how-to-boost-your-author-seo-in-wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:69:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-boost-your-author-seo-in-wordpress/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 18 Jan 2024 14:08:13 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"SEO Tips\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"author seo\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"google eeat\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=268305\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:435:\"<p>What is author SEO, and why should you bother implementing it? One of the criteria Google uses to rank content is its E-E-A-T content quality guidelines. And these completely depend on author SEO. In this article, we’ll show you what&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-boost-your-author-seo-in-wordpress/\">How to Boost Your Author SEO in WordPress</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Kato Nkhoma\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:21745:\"<p>What is author SEO, and why should you bother implementing it?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the criteria Google uses to rank content is its E-E-A-T content quality guidelines. And these completely depend on author SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this article, we’ll show you what author SEO is, it’s importance, and how to implement it so you meet Google’s E-E-A-T standards.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What is Author SEO?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Author SEO is the practice of optimizing your online presence to improve your visibility in <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/what-are-serps/\" title=\"What Are SERPs (And Why Are they Important to SEO)?\">search engine results pages</a> (SERPs) when people search for your name or work. It’s also essential in helping you rank your content for the topics you write about. This is particularly true for YMYL (your money, your life) niches.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Why is Author SEO Important?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>One reason author SEO is important is because it helps you meet Google’s E-E-A-T content guidelines. To ensure users get the best experience when searching for information online, Google introduced E-E-A-T in their <a href=\"https://static.googleusercontent.com/media/guidelines.raterhub.com/en//searchqualityevaluatorguidelines.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">Search Quality Evaluator Guidelines</a>. These are to ensure the content published online is of high quality. E-E-A-T is an acronym that stands for:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Experience</strong> refers to the first-hand experiences the author or other team members have with that particular topic.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Expertise</strong> refers to the expertise of the creator of the main content.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><b>Authoritativeness</b> refers to the authoritativeness of the main content creator, the content, and the website on which the content is published.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Trustworthiness</strong> Refers to the trustworthiness of the main content creator, the content itself, and the website it’s published on.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>The purpose of these standards is to help improve the quality of content published on the web. In addition, it helps ensure that content is accurate and helpful to users.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>While not a direct ranking factor, aligning with Google’s E-E-A-T content quality guidelines does give your content an advantage over your competitors.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How to Use the Author SEO Module in WordPress</h2>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 1: Install All In One SEO (AIOSEO)</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The first step to impactful author SEO is downloading and installing <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"All in One SEO - WordPress SEO Plugin and Toolkit\" rel=\"noopener\">All In One SEO</a> (AIOSEO).&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"462\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/aioseo-wordpress-plugin-homepage-1024x462.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO is a powerful plugin that can help boost author SEO.\" class=\"wp-image-218606\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/aioseo-wordpress-plugin-homepage-1024x462.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/aioseo-wordpress-plugin-homepage-300x135.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/aioseo-wordpress-plugin-homepage-768x347.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/aioseo-wordpress-plugin-homepage-600x271.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/aioseo-wordpress-plugin-homepage-133x60.png 133w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/aioseo-wordpress-plugin-homepage-199x90.png 199w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/aioseo-wordpress-plugin-homepage.png 1116w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\">AIOSEO</a> is a powerful, easy-to-use SEO plugin boasting over 3 million active installs. That means millions of smart bloggers and marketers use AIOSEO to help them boost their search engine rankings and drive qualified traffic to their blogs. The plugin has many powerful features and modules designed to help you properly configure your SEO settings. Examples include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/what-is-cornerstone-content/\" title=\"What is Cornerstone Content? Plus Tips and Examples\">Cornerstone Content</a></strong>: Easily build topic clusters and enhance your topical authority and semantic SEO strategy.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-revisions/\" title=\"SEO Revisions\">SEO Revisions</a>:</strong> Track any changes you make to your site and see their impact on your SEO. Plus, you get to see on a timeline how Google updates affect your site.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/robots-editor/\" title=\"Robots.txt Editor\">Advanced Robots.txt Generator</a></strong>: Easily generate and customize your robots.txt file for better crawling and indexing.&nbsp;</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/truseo-score-analysis/\" title=\"TruSEO On-Page Analysis\">TruSEO Highlighter</a></strong>: Makes it easy to spot on-page SEO issues and gives recommendations for fixing them.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/announcing-aioseo-4-2-5-next-gen-schema-generator-to-improve-your-seo-rankings/\" title=\"Announcing AIOSEO 4.2.5: Next-Gen Schema Generator to Improve Your SEO Rankings\">Next-gen Schema generator</a></strong>: This no-code schema generator enables users to generate and output any schema markup on your site.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong><strong><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/redirection-manager/\" title=\"Redirection Manager\">Redirection Manager</a></strong></strong>: Helps you manage redirects and eliminate 404 errors, making it easier for search engines to crawl and index your site.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/internal-link-assistant/\" title=\"Link Assistant\">Link Assistant</a></strong>: Powerful internal linking tool that automates building links between pages on your site. It also gives you an audit of outbound links.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/what-is-the-seo-preview-tool/\"><strong>SEO Preview</strong></a>: This gives you an overview of your search and social snippets and general SEO so you can improve your optimization.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/indexnow/\" title=\"IndexNow\">IndexNow</a></strong>: For fast indexing on search engines that support the IndexNow protocol (like Bing and Yandex).</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/smart-xml-sitemaps/\" title=\"Smart XML Sitemaps\">Sitemap generator</a></strong>: Automatically generate different types of sitemaps to notify all search engines of any updates on your site.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/\" title=\"Features\">And more</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO also has many other features to help you boost your local SEO, on-page SEO, and technical SEO. And, if you’re a WooCommerce user, AIOSEO has a <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/woocommerce-seo/\">tailor-made WooCommerce SEO module</a> to help you rank your online store higher in search rankings.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Besides these, AIOSEO has a dedicated <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/author-seo-google-e-e-a-t/\" title=\"Author SEO – Google E-E-A-T Addon\"><strong>Author SEO</strong> module</a> to help you implement Google E-E-A-T right in WordPress.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 2: Create a User Profile</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If you haven’t set up user profiles on your WordPress site yet, now would be a great time. To do that, go to your <strong>WordPress dashboard <strong>»</strong> Users <strong>»</strong> Add New User</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"495\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-seo-add-user-1.png\" alt=\"Adding a user\" class=\"wp-image-271499\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-seo-add-user-1.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-seo-add-user-1-300x212.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-seo-add-user-1-600x423.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Fill in all the required information and click the <strong>Add New User</strong> button.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"411\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-seo-add-user-2.png\" alt=\"Click on the Add New User button.\" class=\"wp-image-271500\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-seo-add-user-2.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-seo-add-user-2-300x176.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-seo-add-user-2-600x351.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>And that’s it! You’ve added a user profile.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 3: Add Author Information in the Author SEO Section</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>With AIOSEO installed and your user profiles set up, the next step is to go to the Author SEO section in the Users menu of your WordPress dashboard.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"589\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-seo-1-1024x589.png\" alt=\"Author SEO tab\" class=\"wp-image-271507\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-seo-1-1024x589.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-seo-1-300x173.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-seo-1-768x442.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-seo-1-600x345.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-seo-1.png 1324w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In the Author SEO section, you can add an author’s information to help validate your E-E-A-T signals.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"496\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-info-1.png\" alt=\"Author info section\n\" class=\"wp-image-268293\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-info-1.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-info-1-300x212.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-info-1-600x424.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Some of the author info you can add include</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Alumni Of</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Employer</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Job Title</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>The best part is that AIOSEO outputs <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/what-is-structured-data-and-how-does-it-impact-seo/\" title=\"What is Structured Data and How Does it Impact SEO?\">JSON schema</a> for this information. As a result, search engines can easily understand it and consider it when ranking your content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Besides your credentials and role in your organization, you can also add categories of your areas of expertise.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"238\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/knows-about-section.png\" alt=\"Knows about section/ areas of expertise.\n \" class=\"wp-image-268294\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/knows-about-section.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/knows-about-section-300x102.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/knows-about-section-600x203.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>All this information points to your experience and expertise in your field.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The author bio section allows you to add your author image, an excerpt, and a full bio.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"552\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-info-2.png\" alt=\"Author bio section.\" class=\"wp-image-268295\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-info-2.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-info-2-300x236.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-info-2-600x472.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Coupled with the JSON schema markup, this information proves to search engines that you’re qualified to talk about the subject. This helps you rank higher in searches around your keyword.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 4: Add Author Blocks in Your Posts</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you’ve filled in your author information, the next step to impactful author SEO is to add AIOSEO’s author blocks to your posts. These blocks help you inject the information from the Author SEO section into a post.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO supports 2 main types of author blocks:</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">The Written By Author Block</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>One way of leveraging your bio is by adding an <strong>Author Name</strong> or Written By author block. This gives a very brief summary of the post’s author.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"408\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-bio-tooltip.png\" alt=\"Wriiten by Block\" class=\"wp-image-268296\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-bio-tooltip.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-bio-tooltip-300x174.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-bio-tooltip-600x349.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Hovering over the author&#8217;s name reveals a tooltip with a mini bio.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To add this block, open your post in editor mode, click where you want to place it and insert the block.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"526\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-seo-author-name-block.png\" alt=\"Author name block\" class=\"wp-image-271508\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-seo-author-name-block.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-seo-author-name-block-300x225.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-seo-author-name-block-600x450.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This block pulls from the Author Excerpt field in your Author SEO input.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">The Author Bio Block</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also add an author bio at the bottom of your page. By default, this will be a compact bio.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"388\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/eeat-bio-example.png\" alt=\"Author bio example\" class=\"wp-image-268297\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/eeat-bio-example.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/eeat-bio-example-300x166.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/eeat-bio-example-600x332.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This gives a brief summary of the author. It also:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Links to the author&#8217;s archive page (page with all the author’s articles)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Showcases your areas of expertise</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Links to your social media accounts</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>You can display the full bio by going to the <strong>Author Bio</strong> block settings and turning the <strong>Show Compact Author Bio</strong> toggle off.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"597\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/compact-bio-toggle.png\" alt=\"&quot;Show Compact Author Bio&quot; toggle\" class=\"wp-image-268298\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/compact-bio-toggle.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/compact-bio-toggle-300x255.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/compact-bio-toggle-600x510.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This results in your full bio being displayed:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"684\" height=\"666\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-bio-2-1.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-268291\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-bio-2-1.png 684w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-bio-2-1-300x292.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-bio-2-1-600x584.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 684px) 100vw, 684px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Both the <strong>Author Name</strong> and <strong>Author Bio</strong> blocks help you demonstrate your expertise, experience, authority, and trustworthiness. As a result, meeting Google’s E-E-A-T guidelines is easier.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Trust is one of the key pillars in Google’s E-E-A-T content guidelines. You can gain it from your readers by letting them know who you are and your areas of expertise.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 5: Add Reviewer Block (Optional)</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Another block you can add using AIOSEO’s <strong>Author SEO</strong> module is the <strong>Reviewer block</strong>. Adding a reviewer is an excellent way to boost credibility and further augment your E-E-A-T signals.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"399\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/reviewer-block.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-268299\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/reviewer-block.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/reviewer-block-300x171.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/reviewer-block-600x341.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This is particularly important for YMYL articles, where you need to demonstrate that your content is accurate, up-to-date, and reliable. A reviewer also shows that your content is backed up by an expert and can be trusted.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To add a reviewer block, open your post in editor mode, click where you want to add it and insert the block.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"544\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-seo-inserting-reviewer-block.png\" alt=\"Reviewer block\" class=\"wp-image-271517\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-seo-inserting-reviewer-block.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-seo-inserting-reviewer-block-300x232.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/author-seo-inserting-reviewer-block-600x465.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: You’ll need to have the reviewer’s profile in the Users and Author SEO sections.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And that’s it!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You’ve implemented Author SEO and demonstrated Google E-E-A-T signals in WordPress.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Author SEO: Your FAQs Answered</h2>\n\n\n\n<div data-schema-only=\"false\" class=\"wp-block-aioseo-faq\"><h3 class=\"aioseo-faq-block-question\">What is Author SEO?</h3><div class=\"aioseo-faq-block-answer\">\n<p>Author SEO refers to the practice of optimizing your online presence and boosting your Google E-E-A-T signals. This gives you an edge and helps to enhance your visibility in search engine results. Author SEO can include optimizing your author bios and showcasing your experience, expertise, authority, and trustworthiness (E-E-A-T). It also involves optimizing your social media profiles to showcase your expertise.</p>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div data-schema-only=\"false\" class=\"wp-block-aioseo-faq\"><h3 class=\"aioseo-faq-block-question\">Why is Author SEO important?</h3><div class=\"aioseo-faq-block-answer\">\n<p>Author SEO is essential for increasing discoverability and building an audience. It also helps you meet Google’s E-E-A-T standards, resulting in better rankings on SERPs.</p>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div data-schema-only=\"false\" class=\"wp-block-aioseo-faq\"><h3 class=\"aioseo-faq-block-question\">Which tool can help me with my author SEO?</h3><div class=\"aioseo-faq-block-answer\">\n<p>The best tool for author SEO is All In One SEO (AIOSEO). It’s a powerful plugin that can help you implement Google’s E-E-A-T guidelines right in WordPress. The plugin also has many other modules to help with other aspects of on-page SEO and technical SEO.</p>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this post has helped you know what author SEO is and how to implement it in WordPress. You may also want to check out other articles on our blog, like our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-for-beginners-wordpress-guide/\" title=\"SEO for Beginners: a Simple WordPress Guide\">beginners’ guide to SEO</a> or our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-checklist/\" title=\"50+ SEO Checklist for WordPress – The Complete Guide\">ultimate WordPress SEO checklist</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you found this article helpful, then please subscribe to our <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/c/AIOSEO\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">YouTube Channel</a>. You’ll find many more helpful tutorials there. You can also follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/aioseopack\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">X (Twitter)</a>, <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/aioseo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">LinkedIn</a>, or <a href=\"https://facebook.com/aioseopack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">Facebook</a> to stay in the loop.</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-boost-your-author-seo-in-wordpress/\">How to Boost Your Author SEO in WordPress</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-boost-your-author-seo-in-wordpress/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:82:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"What is Scannability and How to Use it to Improve Content?\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:88:\"https://aioseo.com/scannability/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=scannability\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://aioseo.com/scannability/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 17 Jan 2024 14:02:14 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"SEO Tips\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Scannability\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:26:\"What is scannable content?\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=271099\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:452:\"<p>If you&#8217;ve been researching how to improve your content, you may have come across the idea of “scannability.” Scannability is powerful enough to tip the balance from online failure to success. In this article, you&#8217;ll learn about scannability and how&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/scannability/\">What is Scannability and How to Use it to Improve Content?</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Sherrie Gossett\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19688:\"<p>If you&#8217;ve been researching how to improve your content, you may have come across the idea of “scannability.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Scannability is powerful enough to tip the balance from online failure to success.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this article, you&#8217;ll learn about scannability and how to use it to achieve your website goals.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group aioseo-table-of-contents has-theme-info-background-color has-background is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow\">\n<p>In This Article</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-aioseo-table-of-contents\"><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-what-is-scannability\">What is Scannability?</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-making-pages-scannable\">Making Pages Scannable</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-why-does-scannability-matter\">Why Does Scannability Matter?</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-when-to-make-content-scannable\">When to Make Content Scannable</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-how-to-make-your-content-scannable\">How to Make Your Content Scannable</a><ul></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-improve-readability-with-all-in-one-seo-aioseo\">Improve Scannability With All in One SEO (AIOSEO)</a><ul></ul></li></ul></div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"aioseo-what-is-scannability\">What is Scannability?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Scannability is about making it easy for people to quickly read and understand your website or text. It&#8217;s like arranging things in a way that lets them easily skim through and get the main points without much effort.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The term scannability became popular after a <a href=\"https://www.nngroup.com/articles/how-users-read-on-the-web/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">fascinating study</a> was published by the Nielsen Norman Group in 1997.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Researcher Jakob Nielsen and his team sought to discover how users read on the web.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Their conclusion? &#8220;They don&#8217;t.&#8221;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>&#8220;People rarely read Web pages word by word; instead, they <strong>scan</strong> the page, picking out individual words and sentences.&#8221;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Only a small minority of users in the study read pages word-for-word.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Subsequent research came to the same conclusion.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"aioseo-making-pages-scannable\">Making Pages Scannable</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Nielsen&#8217;s team developed simple guidelines for making pages <strong>scannable</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The goal? <em>Write</em> to help people <em>scan</em>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>These guidelines include using short paragraphs, subheadings, and putting the most important information at the <em>beginning </em>of a page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For a page to be scannable, the <em>formatting must match how users read online</em>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the years since the original study, scannability became a key feature of high-performing content.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"418\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/scannable-content-example-1024x418.jpg\" alt=\"example of scannability\" class=\"wp-image-271116\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/scannable-content-example-1024x418.jpg 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/scannable-content-example-300x122.jpg 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/scannable-content-example-768x313.jpg 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/scannable-content-example-1536x627.jpg 1536w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/scannable-content-example-2048x836.jpg 2048w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/scannable-content-example-600x245.jpg 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/scannable-content-example-147x60.jpg 147w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/scannable-content-example-221x90.jpg 221w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\"><em>This summary helps users decide quickly whether this page is helpful for them. They can immediately opt to explore 2 related topics. (Source:</em><a href=\"https://www.nngroup.com/articles/layer-cake-pattern-scanning/\"> <em>NN/g</em></a><em>)</em></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"aioseo-why-does-scannability-matter\">Why Does Scannability Matter?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Scannability matters because it impacts engagement, conversions, and sales.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>A user will decide whether to leave or stay on a web page within a few seconds.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>A scannable page helps a user determine if the content meets his needs.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For these reasons, scannability is essential for successful content marketing.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"aioseo-when-to-make-content-scannable\">When to Make Content Scannable</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>While scannability will improve most web content, there are some cases where it wouldn&#8217;t be appropriate.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, narrative nonfiction journalism or literature attracts users who want to read word-for-word. And putting the conclusion at the beginning of a novel wouldn&#8217;t make sense.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, even some of this content may benefit from being formatted for easier screen reading.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, editors of the captivating &#8220;<a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/projects/2012/snow-fall/index.html#\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">Snow Fall</a>&#8221; story broke up the long text with short chapter subheadings, video interviews with witnesses, animated graphics, and photos.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>These orient and engage the reader.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"521\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/new-york-times-snowfall-excerpt-1024x521.jpg\" alt=\"new york times snowfall article\" class=\"wp-image-271103\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/new-york-times-snowfall-excerpt-1024x521.jpg 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/new-york-times-snowfall-excerpt-300x153.jpg 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/new-york-times-snowfall-excerpt-768x391.jpg 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/new-york-times-snowfall-excerpt-600x305.jpg 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/new-york-times-snowfall-excerpt-118x60.jpg 118w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/new-york-times-snowfall-excerpt-177x90.jpg 177w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/new-york-times-snowfall-excerpt.jpg 1126w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"aioseo-how-to-make-your-content-scannable\">How to Make Your Content Scannable</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Follow these simple guidelines to make your web pages scannable.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"aioseo-above-the-fold-considerations\">Above-the-Fold Considerations</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Above-the-fold refers to the portion of a web page that&#8217;s visible without scrolling down.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Most users will decide within seconds whether to stay on the page, leave, or click on a link. So, what&#8217;s at the top of a page matters.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Inverted Pyramid</strong>: The Nielsen Norman Group (NN/g) recommends putting your <em>conclusion</em> and most important information at the beginning of your page.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Key Links</strong>: Consider moving the page&#8217;s most important link(s) to the top. Keep those links to a minimum to avoid presenting too many options.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/adding-breadcrumbs-to-your-site-using-the-aioseo-breadcrumbs-block/\"><strong>Breadcrumbs</strong></a>: These tiny navigation links don&#8217;t take up much room. And they can entice readers who decide not to scroll further.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Category Tags</strong>: Place these at the top to engage users who decide not to remain on the page.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-aioseo-theme-notice-box\" role=\"alert\">\n<p>The <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-use-the-inverted-pyramid-to-improve-web-content/\" title=\"\">inverted pyramid approach</a> is copied from news writing. Journalists often place the &#8220;5W and H&#8221; at the beginning: Who, What, How, When, Where, and Why. Details follow.</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"aioseo-below-the-fold\">Below the Fold</h3>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Subheadings: </strong>Break up walls of text with short, descriptive subheadings.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Short paragraphs</strong>: Limit paragraph size to &#8220;<a href=\"https://www.nngroup.com/articles/how-users-read-on-the-web/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">one idea</a>.&#8221;</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Lists</strong>: Vary your formatting by using numbered or bulleted lists where useful.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Bolded text or Italics</strong>: Highlight keywords, but use this technique sparingly.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Stylized Pull Quotes</strong>: With an eye-catching design, short pull quotes can boost scannability. Consider highlighting what&#8217;s unusual or surprising.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Highlight ‘Asides’</strong>: Consider visually highlighting sidebar text to differentiate it from the main flow of the article.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Images and Screengrabs</strong>: These can be useful for breaking up long stretches of text, but images should only be used if they are helpful to the reader. Be cautious when using<a href=\"https://www.nngroup.com/videos/decorative-images/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\"> decorative images</a>.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Visual Data Representation</strong>: Where helpful to the reader, present data visually in charts, tables, or interactive data embeds.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"aioseo-improve-readability-with-all-in-one-seo-aioseo\">Improve Scannability With All in One SEO (AIOSEO)</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>To put these ideas into practice, we recommend using <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\" title=\"\">All in One SEO (AIOSEO)</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The plugin analyzes your pages for readability and scannability <em>in addition to SEO</em>. These readability and SEO checks include instructions on what to change.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here&#8217;s how the readability feature works. AIOSEO checks:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Paragraph length</strong>: The target is no more than 120 words per paragraph. Longer passages are difficult for users to read on screens.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Images/videos</strong> in content: If there are none, you&#8217;ll be encouraged to add <em>relevant</em> media.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Sentence length</strong>: AIOSEO checks for excessive sentence length. The target word count is 20.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Subheading distribution</strong>: The plugin checks to ensure you&#8217;re breaking up content with subheadings. It will suggest adding subheads to passages longer than 300 words.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-use-the-flesch-reading-ease-score-to-grow-traffic/\" title=\"\">Flesch Reading Ease</a></strong>: The plugin uses the Flesch-Kincaid readability tests to assess how easy it is to read your content. You&#8217;ll see recommended improvements.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you’ve installed the All in One SEO (AIOSEO) plugin, log in to any WordPress page to get these recommendations.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Your All in One SEO tools will appear to the right of your article.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Click on <strong>Readability,</strong> and you&#8217;ll get suggestions for improvement.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/aioseo-readability.png\" alt=\"aioseo readability\" class=\"wp-image-248393\" style=\"width:352px;height:261px\" width=\"352\" height=\"261\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/aioseo-readability.png 698w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/aioseo-readability-300x222.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/aioseo-readability-600x444.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/aioseo-readability-81x60.png 81w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/aioseo-readability-122x90.png 1